---

🛠️ Quick Setup Guide

1. Choose your domain (e.g., subhashkumar.com).
2. Update the CNAME file with your domain.
3. Add DNS records at your domain registrar.
4. Wait for propagation (may take up to 24 hours).
5. Verify in GitHub Pages settings.
6. Test your domain in a browser.

---

❓ Troubleshooting

Issue Solution
Domain not resolving Check DNS propagation status.
GitHub Pages shows "Unavailable" Ensure CNAME file is in the root branch.
SSL Certificate error Wait 5-10 minutes for GitHub to provision SSL.
Redirects to wrong domain Update DNS records and CNAME file.
Enforce HTTPS not working Enable "Enforce HTTPS" in GitHub Pages settings.

